    /*                                                                      */
    /*       Fullscreen Interactive Directory Shell for UNIX V.2            */
    /*       ===================================================            */
    /*                                                                      */
    /************************************************************************/

    OPTIONS:                see 'fids -?'

    TERMINALs supported:    vt100,  ansi


    FILES:  fids            executable   
                                         
                                         
            fids.docu       this documentation file
            .fids.pf_keys   file for user defined PF_Key's

    ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES:

            TERM            defines the terminal type (vt100,ansi)
            HOME            defines the default directory for 'cd'
            PATH            defines the command search path
            PS1             defines the primary promt string
                            (modified for subsequent shell commands)

    DESCRIPTION:

            FIDS is a full screen command interpreter with one
            or two directories on the screen.

            The names of the files in a directory are displayed
            in a sorted order: first the subdirs are listed with
            a leading reverse displayed 'd' and then the other files
            in a selectable order.
            The reverse displayed filename is the current selected
            file and the user may select any other file by use of
            the cursor keys.
            In the lower right window on the screen the actual
            file parameters are displayed.
            In the upper right window some system informations are
            displayed.

            After the start of FIDS the user is in the DISPLAY_mode:

            - the screen shows the current work directory:
            - the files sorted in alphabetic order
            - the actual screen position is the subdir ".."

            With the <CR> command on a file position , the ^J cmd ,
            the ^N cmd or any alphanumeric character or number the
            FIDS goes in the COMMAND_MODE:

            - the bottom line on the screen is now the Command line
            - the user may type commands , retrieve previously typed
              commands and edit the command line
            - any UNIX command can be executed including "sh" and
              subsequent commands like fids again!





    /************************************************************************/
    /*                                              B.Noeggerath,           */
    /* fids.docu                page 2 of 8         Rel. 2.9     05.01.1990 */
    /*                                                                      */
    /* Commands in the DISPLAY mode:                              '^'=CTRL  */
    /*                                                                      */
    /************************************************************************/


    Command         Function                Description
    --------------- ----------------------- ----------------------------------

    ^C              exit                    Exit fids and go back to UNIX
    exit<CR>


    <CR>            chdir/cmd_mode          If current position is a directory,
                                            then change actual directory to
                                            this directory, else
                                            go to the command_edit_mode.
                                            If the current position is file "."
                                            the screen will be refreshed.

    ^J              retrieve last command   Go to the command_mode and get
    ^K                                      the last user typed command in
                                            the command_line.

    ?               show fids helppages     There are some helppages online
    <ESC>h


    &               split screen            Split the screen vertical and
                                            show 2 directories on screen.
                                            First the current directory
                                            are on both sides.
                                            The actual directory is that,
                                            where the actual position is
                                            reverse displayed.
                                            If there are 2 directories on
                                            the screen then screen is
                                            unsplitted with the actual
                                            directory.

    <TAB>           switch_side             Switch the actual position to the
                                            opposite side on screen, if screen
                                            is in the split screen mode.

    ^W              view or browse file     The file on the actual screen
                                            position will be displayed.
                                            The user can change here from
                                            'ascii' to 'hex'-mode.

    ^E              call editor             The editor 'e' is called with
                                            the file on the actual screen
                                            position.

    ^Z              execute                 The file on the actual screen
                                            position will be executed as
                                            an executable file.
                                            If the actual file is a directory
                                            the chdir cmd is executed.





    /************************************************************************/
    /*                                              B.Noeggerath,           */
    /* fids.docu                page 3 of 8         Rel. 2.9     05.01.1990 */
    /*                                                                      */
    /* Commands in the DISPLAY mode:                              '^'=CTRL  */
    /*                                                                      */
    /************************************************************************/


    Command         Function                Description
    --------------- ----------------------- ----------------------------------

    ^               page up                 Move the screen one page up
            

    ^               page down               Move the screen one page down
            

    ^F              first position          Move the actual position to the
                                            file ".."

    ^L              last position           Move the actual position to the
                                            last file of the directory

    ^T              sort filelisting        One line with the allowed sort_modes
                                            and the actual sort_mode will be
                    (modes: n=name,t=typ,   displayed and the character for the
                            s=size,         new sort_mode is then asked.
                            u=uid,g=gid,    (The subdir's are always sorted by
                      a=acc,m=mod,c=chan)    their names !)

    <Space>         mark the actual file    If the file on the actual screen
                                            position is not a directory,
                                            the filename is marked with a
                                            leading '@' on the screen.
                                            If the file was marked before,
                                            it will be unmarked.
    ^U              unmark all marked files


    ^D              DELETE  file(s)         The file on the actual screen
                                            position may be removed.
                                            The user will be asked again
                                            if he want to remove the file.
                                            If the actual file is marked all
                                            the marked files may be removed.

    ^N              file_name to cmd_line   Copy the filename on the actual
                                            screen position in the cmd_line
                                            and go to the cmd_mode.
                                            If the actual file is marked
                                            all marked filesnames are copied
                                            in the command line.

    ^P              copy the actual file    same as you type:  cp^N^U
             

    ^O              move the actual file    same as you type:  mv^N^U
              





    /************************************************************************/
    /*                                              B.Noeggerath,           */
    /* fids.docu                page 4 of 8         Rel. 2.9     05.01.1990 */
    /*                                                                      */
    /* Commands in the DISPLAY mode:                              '^'=CTRL  */
    /*                                                                      */
    /************************************************************************/


    Command         Function                Description
    --------------- ----------------------- ----------------------------------

    <ESC>?          escape commands         ? means exact one character:
                                            If ? is not one of the characters
                                            below ( or time after ESC > 1sec )
                                            a line with the allowed characters
                                            will be displayed and then the
                                            wanted character can be reentered.

                                            If ? is an allowed character the
                                            corresponding function will be
                                            executed immediately !

                    ? = 1...9 PF_Keys       Execute user programmable function
                                            as loaded from the PF_file.


                    ? = h : show help_page
              

                    ? = l : load            Load the PF_key definitions
                                            from file ".fids.pf_keys".
                                            This file will be searched first
                                            in the current directory , then
                                            in the home directory and then
                                            along the "PATH".

                    ? = s : save            Save the current directory name


                    ? = r : reset           Reset the previously saved
                                            directory.
                                            ( default saved directory is
                                              the start directory ! )

                    ? = n : change name     The UNIX cmd 'mv' with the actual
                                            filename is set in the command line
                                            for editing and execution.

                    ? = u : change uid      The UNIX cmd 'chown' with the actual
                                            file_uid is set in the command line
                                            for editing and execution.

                    ? = g : change gid      The UNIX cmd 'chgrp' with the actual
                                            file_grp is set in the command line
                                            for editing and execution.

                    ? = m : change mode     The UNIX cmd 'chmod' with the actual
                                            filemode is set in the command line
                                            for editing and execution.





    /************************************************************************/
    /*                                              B.Noeggerath,           */
    /* fids.docu                page 5 of 8         Rel. 2.9     05.01.1990 */
    /*                                                                      */
    /* Commands in the COMMAND mode:                              '^'=CTRL  */
    /*                                                                      */
    /************************************************************************/


    Command         Function                Description
    --------------- ----------------------- ----------------------------------

    ^C              exit                    Exit the command mode and
                                            go back to the display mode

    <CR>            execute command line    The command typed in the cmd_line
                                            will be executed and after return
                                            fids is back in display mode.

    ^J              retrieve last command   Get the previously entered command
                                            in the command line

    @               use each marked file    The char ' @ ' in the command line
                                            will be replaced by one marked file
                                            in the current directory.
                                            The command is executed for all
                                            marked files one after another.

                            example:        cp @ $HOME/bin<CR>
                                            The command cp "name" $HOME/bin
                                            will be executed for each marked
                                            file in the actual directory.

    ^N              insert filename(s)      Insert the filename on the actual
                                            screen position in the cmd_line.
                                            If the actual file is marked
                                            all marked filesnames are inserted
                                            in the cmd_line up to the length
                                            of the cmd_line.

    ^L              insert dir_left         Insert the name of the directory
                                            on the left side on screen in the
                                            cmd_line.

    ^R              insert dir_right        Insert the name of the directory
                                            on the right side on screen in the
                                            cmd_line if screen is in the
                                            split screen mode.

    ^W              insert working dir      Insert the name of the current
                                            working directory in the cmd_line.

    ^U              insert not working dir  Insert the name of the directory
                                            that is not the current work dir.

    ^P              copy the actual file    same as you type:  cp^N^U
            

    ^O              move the actual file    same as you type:  mv^N^U
               





    /************************************************************************/
    /*                                              B.Noeggerath,           */
    /* fids.docu                page 6 of 8         Rel. 2.9     05.01.1990 */
    /*                                                                      */
    /* Commands in the COMMAND mode:                              '^'=CTRL  */
    /*                                                                      */
    /************************************************************************/


    Command         Function                Description
    --------------- ----------------------- ----------------------------------


    ^B              move to begin of line   Move the cursor to the first
                                            character in the command line.



    ^E              move to end of line     Move the cursor behind the last
                                            character in the command line.



    <TAB>           move end/begin of line  Move the cursor to the end of line
                                            if the current position is not eol,
                                            else move cursor to begin of line.



    <CURSOR up>     insert a blank          Insert a blank in the command line
                                            at the current position of cursor.


    <CURSOR down>   delete character        Delete the character in cmd_line
                                            at the current position of cursor.


    ^H              delete character left   Delete the character left of
    <BS>                                    the cursor in the command line.
    <DEL>



    ^D              delete to end of line   Delete all charcaters in cmd_line
                                            from the current cursor position
                                            to the end of cmd_line.


    ^X              delete command line     Delete all charcaters in the
                                            command line.


    <ESC>h          show next helppage      There are some helppages online.




